// ============================================================================
// StrikeZone — Bias Flip (MSA + EMA) v6
// ============================================================================
//
// PURPOSE:
//   A "Bias Flip" / "Regime Switch" alert layer that combines:
//     1) Market Structure Analysis (swing pivots, BOS/CHoCH, trend state)
//     2) EMA 21/55 trend filtering
//   into a unified bias signal. It tells you: "What side of the market
//   should I be on RIGHT NOW?" — and alerts you the moment that changes.
//
// HOW IT WORKS (Mental Model):
//   Think of it like a traffic light for your trading bias:
//     - GREEN (Bullish Bias): Structure flipped bullish + EMA confirms uptrend
//     - RED   (Bearish Bias): Structure flipped bearish + EMA confirms downtrend
//     - GRAY  (Unknown):      Waiting for first confirmed flip
//
//   The key insight is that we DON'T flip on every BOS or CHoCH. We only flip
//   when a REVERSAL signal (CHoCH) occurs AND the EMA trend agrees. This filters
//   out a lot of noise and false reversals.
//
// ARCHITECTURE:
//   The indicator runs THREE state machines in parallel:
//     1) trendState  — MSA's raw structure direction (+1 bull, -1 bear, 0 init)
//     2) emaTrend    — EMA fast vs slow alignment (+1 bull, -1 bear)
//     3) biasState   — The FINAL output bias (+1 bull, -1 bear, 0 unknown)
//
//   biasState only changes when specific conditions align (configurable via
//   confirmationMode input). This is the value you trade.
//
// ALERT SYSTEM:
//   Fires Discord-compatible JSON webhook alerts via alert() with:
//   - Rich embed cards with colored sidebar (green/red/orange)
//   - Structured fields: Symbol, TF, Mode, Reason, Levels, Action, etc.
//   - Fallback to clean markdown "content" mode if embeds disabled
//   - Compact mode option for shorter, scannable alerts
//   - Non-repainting (barstate.isconfirmed + freq_once_per_bar_close)
//
// Author: Built with Pine Script v6 best practices
// Version: 2.0 (Embed Alert Upgrade)
// ============================================================================

//@version=6
indicator("StrikeZone — Bias Flip (MSA + EMA) v6",
     shorttitle = "SZ Bias Flip",
     overlay    = true,
     max_lines_count  = 500,
     max_labels_count = 500)

// ============================================================================
// SECTION 1: USER INPUTS
// ============================================================================
// We organize inputs into logical groups. This isn't just cosmetic — it makes
// the Settings panel in TradingView much easier to navigate. Each group maps
// to a "tab" in the settings dialog.
//
// PRO TIP FOR NEW DEVS: The `tooltip` parameter is your documentation layer.
// Users hover over the (?) icon and see your explanation. Always write tooltips
// as if the user has never seen your indicator before.
// ============================================================================

